1
00:00:17,208 --> 00:00:19,916
[Maka]
A sound soul...

2
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:22,208
...dwells within a sound mind...

3
00:00:22,291 --> 00:00:24,958
...and a sound body.

4
00:00:35,791 --> 00:00:38,375
[chains rattling]

5
00:00:38,458 --> 00:00:40,416
[Free]
It's not far off...

6
00:00:40,500 --> 00:00:41,875
We're here.

7
00:00:42,375 --> 00:00:47,333
♪ opening song ♪

8
00:02:14,666 --> 00:02:16,250
[Stein]
We're running out of time.

9
00:02:16,333 --> 00:02:18,375
We need to get Medusa
out of the way and catch up

10
00:02:18,458 --> 00:02:21,375
with the others to stop
the Kishin from reviving.

11
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,250
[Medusa laughs]

12
00:02:24,333 --> 00:02:25,916
[Medusa]
Got you!

13
00:02:29,750 --> 00:02:31,541
Here she comes!

14
00:02:38,625 --> 00:02:40,625
[Medusa laughs]

15
00:02:40,708 --> 00:02:42,500
[Stein thinks] No matter
how she twists and turns,

16
00:02:42,583 --> 00:02:45,791
the snakes underneath her
always keep her balanced...

17
00:02:45,875 --> 00:02:48,958
This woman leaves no openings.

18
00:02:49,041 --> 00:02:50,666
What now?

19
00:02:50,750 --> 00:02:52,000
[Death Scythe]
Medusa hasn't made any

20
00:02:52,083 --> 00:02:54,458
attempts at all to put
an end to this fight.

21
00:02:54,541 --> 00:02:58,416
She's just trying to buy time
by keeping us occupied here.

22
00:03:01,083 --> 00:03:02,875
[Stein thinks]
She's an intuitive witch...

23
00:03:02,958 --> 00:03:05,375
She probably knows that I
won't be able to defeat her

24
00:03:05,458 --> 00:03:09,333
if my head is full
of disturbing thoughts.

25
00:03:09,416 --> 00:03:11,708
Stein, what's
going on with you...?

26
00:03:11,791 --> 00:03:13,791
It seems like you're
losing your edge...

27
00:03:13,875 --> 00:03:14,958
What happened to that ominous

28
00:03:15,041 --> 00:03:18,291
"I'll kill you" vibe you
used to give off?

29
00:03:18,916 --> 00:03:20,583
Quiet, Spirit...

30
00:03:20,666 --> 00:03:24,208
That's exactly what I'm
trying to work on right now.

31
00:03:27,208 --> 00:03:28,458
I'm paying too much attention

32
00:03:28,541 --> 00:03:32,375
to everything that's
going on around me.

33
00:03:32,458 --> 00:03:35,375
I need to get rid
of irrelevant thoughts.

34
00:03:36,875 --> 00:03:40,458
What drives me is curiosity.

35
00:03:40,541 --> 00:03:42,000
I always do my best work when

36
00:03:42,083 --> 00:03:45,208
the subject at
hand intrigues me.

37
00:03:46,291 --> 00:03:48,541
That's what I need to focus on.

38
00:03:59,250 --> 00:04:02,416
The tension is starting
to leave his body.

39
00:04:10,083 --> 00:04:12,916
He may be the DWMA's
greatest meister...

40
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:16,875
but he's an easy guy to read
if you know what to look for.

41
00:04:16,958 --> 00:04:19,916
[Stein] What is it I want
to do, you ask?

42
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:23,708
I would think it obvious...

43
00:04:23,791 --> 00:04:27,875
[Death Scythe] It's obvious
you're a sadistic man, Stein.

44
00:04:29,500 --> 00:04:31,458
I want to dissect.

45
00:04:35,333 --> 00:04:36,458
[Maka]
Dead or Alive...!

46
00:04:36,541 --> 00:04:39,500
In the Rift Between
Revival and Dazzlement?

47
00:04:40,750 --> 00:04:41,958
[Medusa chuckles]

48
00:04:42,041 --> 00:04:46,291
Oh, Stein... you're so adorable.

49
00:04:47,416 --> 00:04:49,375
[Death Scythe]
Yeah...

50
00:04:49,458 --> 00:04:52,708
I almost forgot it's my job
to control this head case...

51
00:04:52,791 --> 00:04:54,833
What is the fool up to now?

52
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:58,750
Please, no more.

53
00:04:58,833 --> 00:04:59,916
I'm begging you.

54
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:02,416
I'm gonna tear you
into little pieces...

55
00:05:02,500 --> 00:05:04,833
I wonder how
I should do it, though.

56
00:05:04,916 --> 00:05:05,750
Cut up...?

57
00:05:05,833 --> 00:05:06,916
Or gouge out...?

58
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:09,541
Or simply rip apart?

59
00:05:09,625 --> 00:05:10,875
That's for later, though...

60
00:05:10,958 --> 00:05:14,166
Right now I'll give
you a painless death.

61
00:05:15,833 --> 00:05:18,416
[Young Death Scythe]
Step away!

62
00:05:18,500 --> 00:05:20,750
I think that's enough,
don't you?

63
00:05:20,833 --> 00:05:23,375
Stay out of this, Spirit.

64
00:05:23,458 --> 00:05:26,166
I'm going do
things my way.

65
00:05:26,250 --> 00:05:27,916
So then what...?

66
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:31,333
You're just going to ignore
all the academy's rules?

67
00:05:34,208 --> 00:05:36,708
Well, what is it
you want to do?

68
00:05:36,791 --> 00:05:38,625
Did you think you could
simply do anything you please

69
00:05:38,708 --> 00:05:41,791
once you were in the DWMA?

70
00:05:41,875 --> 00:05:45,083
I wish I lived in a world
that knew nothing of the gods.

71
00:05:45,166 --> 00:05:46,166
Whoa, whoa...

72
00:05:46,250 --> 00:05:48,375
...do you seriously mean that?

73
00:05:48,458 --> 00:05:49,916
Of course not...

74
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:54,250
A world like that
would be... diseased.

75
00:05:55,041 --> 00:05:57,250
[Medusa] I'll say it again,
Professor Stein...

76
00:05:57,333 --> 00:06:00,083
Join my experiment.

77
00:06:00,875 --> 00:06:03,583
This static, unchanging
world doesn't suit you...

78
00:06:03,666 --> 00:06:05,333
You were made
for better than this...

79
00:06:05,416 --> 00:06:08,333
You're a scientist after all.

80
00:06:08,416 --> 00:06:11,208
We can harness the power
of the Kishin together...

81
00:06:11,291 --> 00:06:14,291
We'll change the world
back to what it should be...

82
00:06:14,375 --> 00:06:18,291
...a place where evolution
and progress always reign.

83
00:06:18,375 --> 00:06:20,250
A long time ago...

84
00:06:20,333 --> 00:06:22,833
I was analyzed by a group
of foolish doctors who

85
00:06:22,916 --> 00:06:24,958
feared my violent
tendencies and what they

86
00:06:25,041 --> 00:06:27,750
considered my selfish attitude.

87
00:06:27,833 --> 00:06:30,500
They seemed elated while
they were studying me.

88
00:06:30,583 --> 00:06:31,750
As if they were solving the

89
00:06:31,833 --> 00:06:33,250
crime in a mystery novel.

90
00:06:33,333 --> 00:06:35,541
They'd theorize for hours.

91
00:06:35,625 --> 00:06:39,083
Wondering if something had
traumatized me in my past.

92
00:06:39,166 --> 00:06:42,750
Or if some terrible influence
had come into my life.

93
00:06:46,041 --> 00:06:47,708
That was all nonsense though...

94
00:06:47,791 --> 00:06:50,708
I've loved tearing things apart
from the very beginning.

95
00:06:50,791 --> 00:06:52,041
What's your point, Stein?

96
00:06:52,125 --> 00:06:54,666
Are you trying to compare
me to these doctors?

97
00:06:56,333 --> 00:06:57,791
[Stein]
When I was in kindergarten,

98
00:06:57,875 --> 00:07:00,208
it made me nauseous watching
the other kids as they listened

99
00:07:00,291 --> 00:07:03,083
dutifully to the teacher
and played games.

100
00:07:03,166 --> 00:07:04,416
I would almost puke...

101
00:07:04,500 --> 00:07:05,416
...just from the sight of

102
00:07:05,500 --> 00:07:07,333
everyone focusing
unquestioningly

103
00:07:07,416 --> 00:07:09,458
on the chalkboard while
they took their notes...

104
00:07:09,541 --> 00:07:11,708
not an original
thought in their heads.

105
00:07:11,791 --> 00:07:14,125
What kind of story is
this anyway...?

106
00:07:14,208 --> 00:07:16,708
It's entirely pointless,
not to mention boring...

107
00:07:16,791 --> 00:07:18,500
Makes me want to puke.

108
00:07:29,916 --> 00:07:31,541
Are you mocking me?

109
00:07:31,625 --> 00:07:33,625
If you hate
unoriginality so much,

110
00:07:33,708 --> 00:07:36,166
why are your
attacks so tiresome...?

111
00:07:36,250 --> 00:07:38,916
Really... I'm sleeping here.

112
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:41,458
Now, now, be more patient...

113
00:07:41,541 --> 00:07:43,333
This is my answer to
your invitation,

114
00:07:43,416 --> 00:07:45,625
so you should listen.

115
00:07:46,541 --> 00:07:47,916
My feelings didn't change.

116
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:49,458
As I matured and
grew stronger,

117
00:07:49,541 --> 00:07:50,541
the madness inside of me,

